ASMARA, Eritrea, February 19, 2022/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            Eritrean nationals residing in various countries organized as ‘EPLF-HIGDEF Vision Room’ Paltalk group contributed about 6 million Nakfa in support of the National Association of Eritrean War Disabled Veterans.


                                Supporting families of martyrs and war disabled veterans is the responsibility of every citizen
                            

At the handing over event conducted on 17 February, Mr. Gebrebrham Eyasu, chairman of the association, said that the support attests to the strong attachment the Eritrean people inside the country and abroad have with their country and people as well the respect and honor to their martyrs and war disabled veterans.

Expressing satisfaction for being able to support the war disabled veterans association, Ms. Almaz Debesay and Mr. Yosief Laine, representatives of the Paltalk group from Germany and Sweden respectively, said that supporting families of martyrs and war disabled veterans is the responsibility of every citizens and called for reinforced participation and contribution in the effort. 

The ‘EPLF-HIGDEF Vision Room’ Paltalk group comprising nationals residing in America, Europe, the Middle East and Africa has been extending similar support through the Ministry of Labor and Social Welfare to families of martyrs, the National Association of Eritrean War Disabled Veterans as well as other disadvantaged citizens.